[center][size=6][b]RotaAssist - Smart Combat Assistant | Hekili Alternative for Midnight[/b][/size][/center]

[center][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/yourname/RotaAssist/main/docs/images/banner.png[/img][/center]

[size=4][b]The spiritual successor to rotation helpers, built natively for WoW 12.0 Midnight.[/b][/size]

[b]RotaAssist[/b] is not a fork of Hekili. It is a next-generation intelligent combat assistant designed specifically for World of Warcraft: Midnight (12.0). By leveraging Blizzard's brand-new [b]C_AssistedCombat[/b] API, RotaAssist provides 100% compliance with Blizzard's Terms of Service while offering a visual fidelity and situational awareness far beyond legacy alternatives like SACI or JAC.

[hr]

[size=4][b]Key Features[/b][/size]

[list]
[*] [b]100% TOS Compliant:[/b] Uses only official Blizzard APIs. No memory hacks, no automation.
[*] [b]Revolutionary T-Shaped HUD:[/b] A modern UI layout that centralizes your rotation, cooldowns, resources, and defensives.
[*] [b]Smart APL Forecasting:[/b] Powered by SimulationCraft-based logic, RotaAssist predicts your next 2-3 moves so you can stay ahead of the curve.
[*] [b]Intelligent Cooldown Management:[/b] Dynamic visual alerts when your major abilities are about to become ready.
[*] [b]Defensive Advisor:[/b] Automatic screen alerts based on your current health percentage and specialization thresholds.
[*] [b]Pre-Pull Checklist:[/b] Never forget your Flasks, Food, or Runes again.
[*] [b]Native Multi-Language:[/b] Built-in support for English, Simplified Chinese, and Japanese.
[/list]

[hr]

[size=4][b]Supported Specializations[/b][/size]

Currently supporting:
[list]
[*] [b]Demon Hunter:[/b] Havoc, Vengeance, Devourer (Hero Spec)
[/list]
[i]More classes and specializations are coming in v0.2.0![/i]

[hr]

[size=4][b]Installation & Usage[/b][/size]

[list]
[*] Install via CurseForge or download manually from GitHub.
[*] Use [b]/ra[/b] to open the configuration panel.
[*] Use [b]/ra lock[/b] to toggle UI position locking.
[*] Right-click the display for a quick access context menu.
[/list]

